text: Eunidia jeanneli is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Breuning in 1939. It is known from Tanzania, Somalia, Kenya, Zimbabwe, and South Africa.BioLib.cz - Eunidia. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It's 4½–7 mm long and 1–1⅔ mm wide, and its type locality is Neu-Moschi, in the Kilimanjaro Region of Tanzania. It was named in honor of the French entomologist René Jeannel. ==References== Category:Eunidiini Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Eunidia jeanneli
